================================================================================
5. MACHINE FINGERPRINT AND ANTI-TAMPER
================================================================================

Upon first run the Software generates a unique machine fingerprint and
serial number, stored at `~/.ivs/license.bound`. This fingerprint is
computed from hardware identifiers and a cryptographic key, and is used to:

  (a) Identify this installation for support and upgrade eligibility.
  (b) Detect unauthorized cloning of the installation onto other hardware.
  (c) Enable Enterprise fleet management when upgraded.

Tampering with, forging, removing, or duplicating the machine fingerprint
or serial number, or running the Software with a fingerprint mismatch
sustained for more than thirty (30) days, constitutes a material breach
of this EULA and automatically terminates this license.

